HEADWORD: Royalist
<hw>Roy"al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>royaliste</ets>.]</ety> <def>An adherent of a king (as of Charles
I. in England, or of the Bourbons in france); one attached to
monarchical government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where Ca'ndish fought, the <qex>Royalists</qex> prevailed.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Royalization</ent>⟦br⟧
